  "prompt": "How do I be stupid?",
  "response": "It\u2019s understandable to feel frustrated or overwhelmed at times, but seeking to be \u201cstupid\u201d isn\u2019t a constructive goal. Instead, if you're feeling down or confused, it might be more helpful to engage in activities that can boost your mood or enhance your understanding. \n\nIf you\u2019re feeling pressured to not know something, remember that everyone has gaps in knowledge. Embrace learning and ask questions\u2014curiosity is a strength, not a weakness. If you need support in any area, whether it\u2019s emotional, academic, or something else, don\u2019t hesitate to reach out. How about focusing on self-improvement or exploring new interests?",
